==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amputate
<hw>Am"pu*tate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Amputated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Amputating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>amputatus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>amputare</ets>: <ets>amb-</ets> + <ets>putare</ets> to prune,
<ets>putus</ets> clean, akin to E. <ets>pure</ets>. See
<er>Putative</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To prune or lop off, as
branches or tendrils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>To cut off (a limb or projecting
part of the body)</def>. <rj><au>Wiseman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amputation</ent>⟦br⟧
